svgo_cleanupAttrs_desc.message: Removes redundant whitespaces from attribute values. This will not modify the attribute keys, nor remove them if the value becomes empty after optimization.

svgo_cleanupEnableBackground_desc.message: Removes the enable-background attribute, unless it's used in a filter element

svgo_cleanupIDs_desc.message: Removes unused IDs, and minifys IDs that are referenced by other elements.

svgo_cleanupNumericValues_desc.message: Rounds numeric values, and removes the unit when it's 'px' as this is the default.

svgo_collapsGroups_desc.message: Finds groups that effectively do nothing and flattens them, preserving the contents of the groups.

svgo_convertColors_desc.message: Converts color references to the shortest equivalent.

svgo_convertEllipseToCircle_desc.message: Converts ellipses with equal radiuses to circles.

svgo_convertPathData_desc.message: Optimize path commands found in <path>, <glyph>, and <missing-glyph> elements. Path commands are the syntax used in the d attribute, each character represents an instruction to draw paths.

svgo_convertTransform_desc.message: Collapse multiple transforms into one and convert matrices to the short aliases

svgo_inlineStyles_desc.message: Merges styles from <style> elements to the style attribute of matching elements

svgo_mergePaths_desc.message: Merges multiple paths into one, or into a <g> element if they have the same attributes

svgo_mergeStyles_desc.message: Merges multiple style elements into one

svgo_moveElemsAttrsToGroup_desc.message: Move an elements attributes to their enclosing group

svgo_moveGroupAttrsToElems_desc.message: Move some group attributes to the contained elements

svgo_removeComments_desc.message: Removes XML comments from the document. XML comments are the content between the '<!--' and '-->' syntax, and do not effect rendering

svgo_removeDesc_desc.message: Removes the <desc> element from the document if the <desc> element is empty or appears to only contain editor attribution

svgo_removeDoctype_desc.message: Removes the Document Type Definition, also known as the DOCTYPE, from the svg

svgo_removeEditorsNSData_desc.message: Removes all XML namespaces, elements, and attributes associated with popular vector editing software

svgo_removeEmptyContainers_desc.message: Remove container elements in the document that have no children or meaningful attributes

svgo_removeEmptyText_desc.message: Removes text elements that do not have meaningful attributes

svgo_removeHiddenElems_desc.message: Remove hidden or invisible elements from the document. This can be elements with 0 width and height defined, or elements that were just hidden with CSS

svgo_removeMetadata_desc.message: Removes the <metadata> element from the document. Metadata doesn't effect rendering. From an optimization perspective, these can always be safely removed

svgo_removeNonInheritableGroupAttrs_desc.message: Removes non-inheritable presentation groups from children

svgo_removeTitle_desc.message: Removes the <title> element from the document.

svgo_removeUnknownsAndDefaults_desc.message: Removes unknown elements and attributes, as well as attributes that are set to their default value

svgo_removeUnusedNS_desc.message: Removes unused namespace declarations from the document

svgo_removeUselessDefs_desc.message: Removes children of <defs> element that do not have an ID to reference.

svgo_removeUselessStrokeAndFill_desc.message: Removes useless stroke and fill attributes

svgo_sortAttrs_desc.message: Sorts attributes in all elements in the document. This does not reduce the size of the SVG, but improves readability and may improve how compression algorithms perform on it

svgo_sortDefsChildren_desc.message: Sorts all children in the '<defs>' element. This does not reduce the size of the SVG, but may improve how compression algorithms perform on it

svgo_removeViewBox_desc.message: Removes the viewBox attribute when height and width is identical

svgo_cleanupListOfValues_desc.message: Rounds numeric values in attributes, such as those found in viewBox, enable-background, and points

svgo_convertOneStopGradients_desc.message: Converts the <linearGradient> and <radialGradient> nodes that are effectively a solid color to the color

svgo_convertStyleToAttrs_desc.message: Converts presentation attributes in element styles to the equvilent XML attribute

svgo_prefixIds_desc.message: Prefix element IDs and class names with the provided file name. Defaults to 'prefix__'

svgo_removeDimensions_desc.message: Removes the width and height attribute from the top-most <svg> element if specified, and replaces it with the viewBox attribute if it's missing

svgo_removeOffCanvasPaths_desc.message: Removes <path> elements that are drawn outside of a viewBox

svgo_removeRasterImages_desc.message: Removes inline JPEGs, PNGs, and GIFs from the document

svgo_removeXMLNS_desc.message: Removes the xmlns attribute from the top-most <svg> element in the document

svgo_reusePaths_desc.message: Creates a definition for similar paths, and swaps the <path> elements to <use> elements that will reference a single <path> definition

export_prefix_names_tooltip.message: Override associated icon names with an enumerated prefix

settings_merge_label.message: Merge collections with the same source URL

settings_merge_tooltip.message: Automatically merge collections with identical SVGs that shares the same source URL

settings_importing_desc.message: Default configuration settings for importing collections.

settings_collections_desc.message: Settings and configuration options for data and collection history

settings_reset_desc.message: Clear all collections and data from local storage related to SVG Gobbler. This will reset SVG Gobbler to initialized state

settings_export_data_desc.message: Download all collections and data from local storage related to SVG Gobbler. This will create a JSON file that contains all information stored.
